{"id":"adversary","term":"Adversary","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>(Heb. satan), an opponent or foe (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Kings 5:4\">1 Kings 5:4</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Kings 11:14\">11:14</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Kings 11:23\">23</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Kings 11:25\">25</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Luke 13:17\">Luke 13:17</a>); one that speaks against another, a complainant (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 5:25\">Matt. 5:25</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Luke 12:58\">Luke 12:58</a>); an enemy (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Luke 18:3\">Luke 18:3</a>), and specially the devil (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Peter 5:8\">1 Pet. 5:8</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["1 Kings 5:4","1 Kings 11:14","1 Kings 11:23","1 Kings 11:25","Luke 13:17","Matthew 5:25","Luke 12:58","Luke 18:3","1 Peter 5:8"]}